    "content": "MEETING RECAP – ACCESS CONTROL\nMay 5, 2026\nI. MTB parking\n- All the staff and workers will use Face ID this wek. IT to make sure 100% of the staff registered\nthis week.\n- Punch list: GD requested our cooperation to fix minor issues where possible.\nII. Access control for people\n- Target: control how people enter the terminal.\n- Primary focus: for our staff and contractors who are regular daily users.\n- Secondary / exception cases: Guests, agents, authorites and visitors.\n1. Turnstile: proper 2 turnstile with 2 way direction in current position.\nWe need a drop-up turnstile like now, but with 4 sections instead of 3. This helps make sure only one\nperson can pass at a time, so people can’t go together.\n2. The system support diverse authentication method: Faceid/ fingerprint and card, but integrated in 1\nmachine\n3. Registration\nCurrent process:\n- Customers send access requests via email to OPS\n- Operations reviews and approves/rejects requests\n- Approved requests are passed to HSSE to control\n- HSSE to control access by checking manually ID cards and information provided by OPS.\n- HR also use STOS to cross- check the working hours and calculate payroll.\nThe system is required:\n- Upload data in batch to the system\n- Time-bound access control (start/end dates)\n- Automatically block access when expired\n- Data history and generate access report\n- Send data, real time data sharing with STOS.\n4. Later review:\n- How to handle passengers inside vehicles.\nIII. Vehicle cotrol:\n1. Vehicle control will be implemented at main gate and side gate at the same time.\n2. Proposed layout: 2 lanes in/ 2 lanes out\n3. Barrier is required to stop the truck in the right place.\n4. Barrier control for lane-in:\n+ Barrier opens only when:\n- Security physically checks the truck\n- If approved, security confirms in the system\n- Then barrier is opened via a button or touch screen\n- System must already show the truck is valid and allowed entry\nFor agribulk trucks\n- Security must physically inspect the truck\n- After inspection, HSSE confirms in system → barrier opens\nFor Woodchip trucks\n- Can allow trucks goinging in since trucks are full\n5. Barrier control for lane-out.\n- Weigh slip/ticket is printed.\n- Security checks the slip and then opens the gate.\n6. Requirement: Data can be sent in real-time from STOS/ scale system to the new software.\n7. To control truck get out, CICT want to check the trunk/ take picture if there is cargo inside or not. We\nneed to see if AI camera could do that.\nConclusion: BOD and department would continue to work to complete our scope of work before sending out\ntender letter.\n-----------------------------------"
