    "absolute_original_path": "C:\\Users\\DUKE NGUYEN\\Desktop\\3. Các dự án tiếp\\Project 2&3 summary Apr 2026.docx",
    "domain": "Khác / Chung",
    "doc_type": "Tài liệu nghiệp vụ / Báo cáo",
    "language": "Tiếng Anh (EN)",
    "year": 2026,
    "content": "**Project No. 2 (Access Control – People)**\n\n**1. Physical Gate Devices**\n\n• **VHB**: Swing gates with high glass panels to prevent climbing.\n\n**• Sao Bac Dau (SBD):** Flap barriers with dual infrared sensors.\n\n• **IHN** (SmartGate): Tripod turnstiles combined with face recognition and QR codes.\n\n• Hoang Phat: Flat barriers.\n\n**2. Authentication Technology**\n\n• **VHB**: Hikvision Face ID devices supporting face, fingerprint, and RFID with liveness detection.\n\n• Sao Bac Dau (SBD): Industrial-grade Face ID with liveness detection, QR/NFC ID registration, and blacklist alerts.\n\n• **IHN (**SmartGate): Combination of Face ID and QR code.\n\n• **Hoang Phat**: Face or fingerprint recognition.\n\n**3. Anti-tailgating Mechanism**\n\n• **Sao Bac Dau** (SBD): Strongest solution with AI + dual IR sensors, reducing risk to near 0%.\n\n• **VHB**: Built-in sensors ensure only one person per authentication cycle.\n\n• **IHN** (SmartGate): Tripod mechanism and sensors prevent multiple people passing.\n\n**4. User Registration (Visitors/Contractors)**\n\n• **VHB**: Self-service kiosk with ID scan (QR/NFC), automatic data extraction and face capture – very good option.\n\n• **Sao** **Bac** **Dau** (SBD): Manual register & Supports training to improve recognition accuracy.\n\n• **IHN** (SmartGate): 3-step process: Manual register → scan → gate opens.\n\n• **Hoang** **Phat**: Manual face/fingerprint registration before access.\n\n**5. Integration and Expansion**\n\n• **VHB**: Provides API and centralized data management.\n\n• **Sao** **Bac** **Dau** (SBD): Strong multi-system integration (CCTV, PA, HRM, ERP) with Smart Port vision.\n\n• **Hoang** **Phat**: Oracle ERP integration.\n\n• **IHN** (SmartGate): Unified interface with existing vehicle control system.\n\n**Summary:**\n\n• **SBD**: Best anti-tailgating and system integration vision.\n\n• **VHB**: Strong physical security and modern kiosk automation.\n\n• **IHN**: Focus on convenience and system consistency.\n\n• **Hoang** **Phat**: Strong operational processes and ERP experience.\n\n**Project No. 3 (Vehicle Control – Container Trucks and Cars)**\n\nThere are four main vendors/solutions proposed: VHB, Sao Bac Dau (SBD), Hoang Phat, and SmartGate (IHN). Below is a detailed comparison of these solutions:\n\n**1. Core Identification and Authentication Technology**\n\n• **VHB**: Uses long-range UHF tags attached to vehicle windshields as the sole determinant for automatic barrier opening. LPR cameras are only used for post-checking and mismatch alerts.\n\n• **Sao Bac Dau** (SBD): Combines specialized ANPR cameras for heavy trucks with RFID for frequent vehicles. The key differentiator is Vision + Weight Fusion (AI image + weighbridge data) to achieve optimal accuracy.\n\n• **Hoang Phat**: Focuses on RFID readers for automatic vehicle identification combined with management software to control barrier opening/closing.\n\n• SmartGate (**IHN**): Simultaneously verifies both UHF readers and LPR cameras within a 0–5 meter range when vehicles enter the scanning zone.\n\n**2. AI Applications and Container Inspection**\n\n• **VHB**: Proposes additional panoramic cameras and AI modules to detect whether vehicles carry containers.\n\n• **Sao Bac Dau** (SBD): Strong AI capabilities to recognize container numbers, detect open containers, classify 20ft/40ft containers, and detect door direction.\n\n• SmartGate (**IHN**): Highlights automated container inspection using high-resolution top-mounted cameras and computer vision to analyze cargo quantity inside.\n\n• **Hoang Phat**: Mainly focuses on operations and data storage, with limited emphasis on deep AI container analysis.\n\n**3. Infrastructure and Operations**\n\n• **VHB**: Strategically proposes reducing exit lanes from 3 to 2 to avoid traffic conflicts and improve tag reading accuracy. Also suggests using “soft barriers” (rubber poles).\n\n• **Sao Bac Dau** (**SBD**): Emphasizes a two-phase implementation roadmap: Phase 1 for basic control; Phase 2 for AI container and weighbridge fusion.\n\n• **SmartGate** (**IHN**): Designs an integrated system with lane dividers and loop/radar sensors for highly accurate vehicle detection.\n\n**4. System Integration Capability**\n\n• **Hoang Phat**: Strong integration with Oracle ERP (real-time, one-way or two-way).\n\n• **VHB**: Provides APIs for integration with port systems and supports UHF tag retrieval from existing systems (VETC/ePass).\n\n• SmartGate (**IHN**): Focuses on integration with port operating systems (TOS/STOS).\n\n• Sao Bac Dau (**SBD**): Aims for an open platform expandable into a Smart Port ecosystem (ERP, HRM, weighbridge).\n\n5. Accuracy Commitment\n\n• **VHB**: 99–100% accuracy (UHF-based).\n\n• Sao Bac Dau (**SBD**): 97–99% accuracy using Fusion technology.\n\n• SmartGate (**IHN**): >98% license plate recognition accuracy.\n\n**Summary:**\n\n• **VHB**: Best for stable barrier control.\n\n• **SBD** & **IHN**: Strong in AI-based container analysis.\n\n• **Hoang** **Phat**: Strong in ERP integration – not very useful in this phase."
