    "content": "## Sheet1\n| Unnamed: 0 | ACCESS CONTROL SYSTEM REQUIREMENT | Unnamed: 2 | Unnamed: 3 | Unnamed: 4 | Unnamed: 5 |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| NaN | NaN | By | Requirement | Comment | Feedback |\n| NaN | 1.0 | IT | Multi-layer authentication: Supports card, fingerprint, facial recognition, or QR code to prevent unauthorized access. | Agreed. | NaN |\n| NaN | 2.0 | IT | Connection with time attendance system: Automatically logs employee check-in/out times. | But access through turnstile is not where attendance is tracked. That should remain next to the safety office and near the elevator. | If the new system can do it, employees will have another option to check in/out. |\n| NaN | 3.0 | IT | Integration with ERP/HRM platforms: Links to workforce data, shift schedules, and payroll. | System must provide option to connect to an ERP system. We don’t have one now, but we may want to link it later. | Sure, we will keep this requirement. |\n| NaN | 4.0 | IT | Scalability & data security: Supports multiple checkpoints and complies with encryption/security standards. | Agreed. | NaN |\n| NaN | 5.0 | IT | For internal staff in the admin building: use AI camera | Maybe also allow for identification by fingerprint or card. | Already mentioned in No1 |\n| NaN | 6.0 | IT | For external users: The vendor can suggest the equipment to control at the turnstile. | We need to tell the vendor what we want. Following several internal discussions, believe we need a combination of face recognition and card (visitors). Perhaps even allow fingerprint. | The best practice is Face ID for internal staff and cards for external. |\n| NaN | NaN | NaN | NaN | NaN | If we use biometrics guests, that would be annoying and difficult to follow up. |\n| NaN | 7.0 | IT | The vendor needs to modify the turnstile to fit with the new system. (details of the turnstile will be sent to the vendor). | This will automatically trigger a new turnstile. We should invite the vendor to study our setup and ask for recommendation, before we decide to replace. Changes we may be able to handle ourselves. | Noted |\n| NaN | 8.0 | IT | Smart proximity sensors: Activates rotation only when a person actually passes through. | If possible, fine. Seems like nice-to-have. | Some properties have this function in their turnstiles. We will work with the vendor on this. |\n| NaN | 9.0 | IT | Easy maintenance & modular design: Simplifies component replacement and reduces downtime. | Agreed. | NaN |\n| NaN | 10.0 | HSSE | Anti-tailgating mechanism: Sensors and automatic locking to ensure only one person passes at a time. | Agree. | NaN |\n| NaN | 11.0 | HSSE | Integrated surveillance cameras: Record all entries/exits and connect to the central security system. | Agree. | NaN |\n| NaN | 12.0 | HSSE | Emergency exit function: Turnstiles must have a fail-safe mode to open during fire or natural disasters. | Agree. | NaN |\n| NaN | 13.0 | OPS | Flexible adjustment of turnstile opening/closing times | Not sure what is meant by this. Turnstile and access system should be up 24/7. Don’t see how that can be flexible. | Confirmed. Delete it. |\n| NaN | 14.0 | NaN | NaN | NaN | NaN |\n| NaN | 15.0 | HR | Ability to recognize and assign work shifts | Same as 12. | Yes, duplicated. |\n| NaN | NaN | NaN | NaN | HR: agree, should integrate  the auto-email function  to employee after assign work shifts. | It should be removed. |\n| NaN | 16.0 | HR | Capability to integrate with the existing time attendance system | Agree. Maybe we will even replace the current attendance system all together. | If it can do this job, it must have the ability to do No12 job. |\n| NaN | 17.0 | HR | Productivity & presence tracking: Turnstile data provides accurate workforce monitoring. | Not sure how this could work. | The idea is: we can track how many people are in the port or in the building. |\n| NaN | 18.0 | EQM | Customizable opening/closing times: Adjustable for peak hours or specific port requirements. | Same as 11. | Adjustable speed of opening or closing is good for both users and maintenance. |\n| NaN | NaN | NaN | Easy to use: Simple authentication (card, PIN, fingerprint, or mobile app) with minimal effort required. | NaN | NaN |\n| NaN | NaN | NaN | Reliable: Operates consistently without failures and always responds quickly and accurately. | NaN | NaN |\n| NaN | NaN | NaN | Secure: Ensures that only authorized personnel can access designated areas and prevents unauthorized entry. | NaN | NaN |\n| NaN | 19.0 | DGD | System should use same interface and hardware as used for the vehicle access control system. | NaN | Noted, Frank. |\n| NaN | NaN | NaN | NaN | NaN | NaN |\n| NaN | 20.0 | MKT | How about customers visit ports? Do we have any system developed to register them (to track how many people in the  building at the same time) or remain manually? | NaN | Same function as No15Including AI camera |\n| NaN | 21.0 | MKT | How about staffs checked in but out for tasks and not checked out, and vice versa? | NaN | This should be handled manually; |\n| NaN | NaN | NaN | NaN | NaN | An approval is a must. |\n| NaN | NaN | NaN | NaN | NaN | => It will be opposite with item 15 as we target to be able to track how many people are in port or building at the same time. Maybe AI camera as above. |\n| NaN | NaN | NaN | NaN | NaN | ==> That’s what we should discuss to the vendor and they will help us out. |\n| NaN | 22.0 | MKT | Can all managers track their staffs’ working day in month via system? | NaN | This function should belong to ERP or HR software. |"
