    "content": "**VEHICLE CONTROL REQUIREMENTS**\n\n**PART I: OVERVIEW OF OPERATIONS & BUSINESS PROCESSES (For Project/Operations Managers)**\n\n**1. Management of Entry/Exit Processes & Vehicle Coordination**\n\nThis section focuses on how the system handles the daily vehicle flow and the features supporting operation staff.\n\n* **Process Automation:** The Gate system must have a standardized, automatic process to minimize manual operations and human errors.\n* **Object Classification:** Supports various vehicle types: Internal vehicles, cargo operation vehicles, ticketed vehicles, guest/contractor vehicles, and different license plate types (Vietnamese, International).\n* **Registration & Approval:**\n + Module allows for remote vehicle list registration (via office).\n + Approval process for the vehicle list by the HSSE (Health, Safety, Security, Environment) department.\n + Supports on-site access granting by security for special cases (official duty vehicles, emergency) but requires mandatory license plate entry for system recording.\n* **Time & Validity Control:**\n + Setting of access validity (from date... to date...).\n + Configuration of port operating hours. Alert if a vehicle attempts to leave the port during prohibited hours (for vehicles currently handling cargo).\n* **Exception Handling:**\n + Allows manual Barrier control when the system fails or for priority vehicles (fire truck, police).\n + The system must operate continuously, allowing manual data entry for cross-checking if RFID is not automatically assigned.\n\n**2. Monitoring & Management Reporting**\n\nProvides management with a comprehensive view of the port's operational status.\n\n* **Real-time Monitoring:**\n + Knowing the exact number of vehicles currently inside the port at any given moment.\n + Filtering data by shift, time frame.\n + Displaying vehicles that are \"stuck\" in the port and have not completed the process (not weighed, not handled cargo, not exited the gate).\n* **Alert System:**\n + Alert for vehicles that have been weighed but have not left the port after a specified time (e.g., > 2 minutes).\n + Alert for vehicles overstaying in the port (High Turnaround time).\n + Alert for vehicles exiting the gate without an entry history.\n* **Detailed Reports:**\n + Report on the list of vehicles by vessel and cargo handling time.\n + Report on vehicle turnaround time to evaluate operational efficiency.\n + Storage of digital evidence (photos, logs) for post-audit purposes.\n\n**3. Security, Safety & Compliance Control (HSSE)**\n\nEnsures area security and compliance with labor safety regulations.\n\n* **Blacklist Control:** The system blocks vehicles forbidden from entering the port or vehicles not yet permitted to leave the port.\n* **Anti-fraud:**\n + Detection of tailgating vehicles to sneak through the gate.\n + Cross-checking the actual license plate (Captured by Camera) and the registered license plate in the smart card (RFID).\n* **Equipment Safety:** Safety sensors ensure the Barrier only lowers when the vehicle has completely passed through.\n* **HSSE Compliance Check:** Integration of automatic safety check procedures (rejecting vehicles with open tailgates, unshielded cargo, lack of PPE...).\n* **Strict Authorization:** Detailed control of system access rights for each user, with an operation history (Audit trail) to know who added/deleted/modified data and when.\n\n**4. System Integration Capability**\n\nThe system does not operate in isolation but is part of the port ecosystem.\n\n* **Hardware Connectivity:** Integration with CCTV cameras, access control (Barrier, gate door), weighing stations.\n* **Software Connectivity:**\n + Integration with the port operation system (STOS/TOS) to retrieve the registered vehicle list from the Portal.\n + Integration with the Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) system.\n\n**PART II: TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS & ADVANCED SOLUTIONS (For IT/Solution Specialists)**\n\nThese are non-functional requirements and specific technical requirements demanding high precision:\n\n**1. Recognition & Image Processing Technology (Advanced OCR/ANPR)**\n\n* **Strict Accuracy:** Recognition accuracy required to be $>99\\%$ during the day and $>98\\%$ at night/bad weather.\n* **Harsh Environment:** Must use Infrared technology or advanced image processing algorithms to operate in complete darkness, fog, rain, or with dirt on the license plate.\n* **Multi-dimensional Processing:** Recognizes vehicles at various speeds and angles.\n* **AI Cargo Inspection:** Uses AI/Computer Vision to detect whether a truck bed is loaded or empty (automating the cargo inspection process).\n\n**2. System Architecture & Infrastructure (Architecture & Infra)**\n\n* **Edge Computing:** The system at the gate must be able to operate independently (Offline mode) when connectivity to the central server is lost; data will be re-synchronized when the network is available.\n* **High Availability & Redundancy:** Requires a backup server, automatic Failover mechanism to ensure maximum continuous operation time (Uptime).\n* **Auto-diagnosis:** The system automatically detects equipment errors (camera, RFID, barrier, network, hard drive) and sends technical alerts.\n* **High Performance (Low Latency):** Processing time at the gate (including ANPR + RFID + database check) must be extremely low (1-2 seconds) to avoid congestion.\n* **Scalability:** Supports high traffic volume (500 - 1000+ vehicles/day) and is easily expandable in the future.\n\n**3. RFID & Anti-Interference Solution**\n\n* **Signal Filtering Algorithm:** Mandatory signal filtering algorithm or physical solution to prevent Cross-read of RFID tags from vehicles in the adjacent lane.\n* **Tamper Detection:** Mechanism to detect if the RFID tag has been removed, swapped, copied, or does not match the recognized license plate.\n\n**4. Security & Data Integration (Security & API)**\n\n* **API Standards:** Provides standard APIs for communication with ERP, STOS.\n* **Data Integrity:** Protects license plate data and images from unauthorized access. The entire history of data intervention must be recorded (Audit Log).\n* **Dual Cross-check Logic:** Automatically compares data from [Camera] vs [RFID] vs [Registration Data] to authenticate the vehicle."
