    "content": "Ask for Feedback\n\nInstructions\n\n*The best way to help team members feel comfortable asking for feedback is to lead by example. Make it a habit to use the following prompts to gather the feedback you need to keep building your skills. Encourage your team members to do the same.*\n\n1. **Score me.** Example: “What score (1-10) would you give my presentation?” followed by, “What could I do next time to bring my score up?”\n\nI will ask my team:\n\nFeedback I received:\n\n1. **One thing.** Example:“What is one thing I could improve on in this presentation/document/design/pitch?\n\nI will ask my team:\n\nFeedback I received:\n\n1. **“So I can learn.”** Example: “Could you please explain your edits on my draft *so I can learn?”* “Can you give me advice on how I could have managed the meeting better *so I can learn*?”\n\nI will ask my team:\n\nFeedback I received:\n\n1. **Stop/start/continue.** Example:“Please tell me something that I should *stop* doing, something I should *start* doing, and something I need to *continue* doing.”\n\nI will ask my team:\n\nFeedback I received:"
